						<summary>

						<p>This is also damaged. It records some gift made by one Kañjappōśaṉ Yajña-Nārāyaṇa-Bhaṭṭaṉ of Vikramaśōḻa-chaturvēdimaṅgalam, which is referred to as a <hi rend="italic">paḷḷi [ppaḍai]</hi> of the king, situated in Tiraimūr-nāḍu, for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple.</p>						

